Show HN: Shifu Brings mobile app development ease to the IoT world
text:
Hi HN,

We're excited to introduce Shifu, a platform that makes IoT development easy and intuitive. We know that traditional multi-device interaction can be complex and time-consuming, because you need to manually integrate all those heterogeneous devices, which is why we've worked hard to create a platform that brings app-like simplicity to the process.

Our platform is cloud-native, extending the resources of Kubernetes through CRD. Shifu creates digital twins to accomplish physical device management, making the development process even more efficient and user-friendly.

Give Shifu a try and see for yourself!

Ask HN: Why was this post flagged – what is the policy on titles?
text:
I don't get it why did this post get flagged https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=33892944

- I've used the original title - nature.com is well known site

I've noticed that sometimes when I change the title I get called upon that fact I people tell in comments that I should use the original title. When I leave the original title sometimes I get comments that the title is clickbait.

So what is the best way to post: with original title or change it? I really don't see what would be the problem with "Direct detection of ultralight dark matter bound to the Sun with space quantum sensors" as title.

Show HN: GPTMarker – Save and share your ChatGPT conversations
text:
Problem: As users engage in conversations with ChatGPT, they often want to save or share their conversations with ChatGPT. However, currently there is no easy way to do this, making it difficult for users to create screenshots and share their conversations.

Solution: GPTMarker is a new tool that allows users to easily save and share their ChatGPT conversations. With GPTMarker, users can simply click a button to save their conversation, and then share it with others via a unique URL. This makes it easy for users to revisit their conversations and share them with others, enhancing their overall ChatGPT experience.

Ask HN: Are things getting more convenient but less satisfying?
text:
I read a post on HN recently where a guy in his teens used to visit a construction site to watch how peopled worked and even help them for small fee. Now he could just watch a YouTube video about it in 10 different ways but the experience differs in that the workers used to treat him well and converse with him, which obviously made him a deep impression.

So I'd be interested to generalize this: with things getting more and more digital and disembodied (ahem, ChatGPT), does it produce convenience at the expense of contentment?

Ask HN: Is there a market use case for DeFi outside of emerging markets?
text:
Hi everyone,

I am job hunting now and it seems like half of the companies reaching out to me are involved with DeFi. I have stayed far away from the crypto space because I have yet to see a valid use case for it in my own life, and of the plethora of scams in the space. I’ve read numerous threads here where people debate the usefulness of DeFi and crypto.

From what I can tell, there is one use case that DeFi is actually useful, and that is acting as the financial infrastructure for people in emerging markets who don’t have access to any traditional banks or lenders. This alone isn’t enough to convince me though because as it stands, anyone with access to traditional finance infra should continue to do so as you get far more assurances through auditing, and US federal support like FDIC.

Can someone explain to me a specific situation in which someone in a western country would want to use DeFi outside of speculative investing?
